30/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski said the country's future is in the principles of co-existence, tolerance and integration, not in conflict, hatred and division.
Meeting Monday (29 December) with leaders of religious communities in the country, Crvenkovski stressed that the session represented a strong message to all citizens that they should unite and work together to achieve the common goal of EU integration.
In other news Monday, Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski said Skopje expects confirmation of NATO's open door policy and verification of membership bids by Macedonia, Albania and Croatia, during the Alliance's June summit in Istanbul.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 30/12/03;
MIA, A1 TV - 29/12/03)
